---------
PRE_INSTALL
----------
Run the following as root to setup a brand new image
---------

Create the bozuko user
--------
adduser bozuko - use the standard password
add user bozuko to sudo group in /etc/group


Set the hostname
-------
hostname <name>


Install git
---------
apt-get install git


logout and log back in as bozuko user
---------


Generate ssh keys as user bozuko
---------------------------
ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "bozuko@<hostname>"


Copy the key and add it to the github bozuko account 
with read-only permissions via the web interface
-------------
cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub



------------
INSTALL
------------
Run the folllowing as user bozuko to install bozuko and it's dependencies.
---------
git clone git@github.com:bozuko/bozuko.git
cd bozuko/install
sudo ./install_privileged.sh
./install.sh
